explanation: Unique identifier used to locate a resource on the Internet. It is also referred to as a web address.
Standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web browser. It defines the content and structure of web content.
A style sheet language used for specifying the presentation and styling of a document written in a markup language such as HTML or XML.

Markup language and file format for storing, transmitting, and reconstructing arbitrary data. It defines a set of rules for encoding documents in a format that is both human-readable and machine-readable.
Text file that has a specific format which allows data to be saved in a table structured format.
